work planning and control policies & procedures skip to main content slac web people slac home slac today for staff for users directorates ets operations lcls particle physics & astrophysics photon science ssrl es & h esh web manual esh home general work planning and control policy 02 work planning and control forms & tools policies contacts publication december 2010 for information about changes please see the revision history chapter 02 work planning and control work planning and control wpc is the use of formalized standardized and documented methods and processes for considering and mitigating risks when planning authorizing releasing and performing work the purpose of wpc is to ensure adequate protection of workers the public and the environment which would otherwise be put at risk by inconsistent and inadequate planning authorization and control using the principles of integrated safety and environmental management wpc emphasizes using a graded approach in the level of coordination required to identify and mitigate hazards to personnel environment and equipment the types of work green yellow red are in turn based on complexity of the work view the entire chapter in a pdf format forms and tools online contacts online please use the pdf for printing your browser does not have the ability to display inline frames you can view the content of this frame at this page slac footer questions submit a web request or last update
